        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): route direct media captions through attachments",
        "body": "## Summary\n- route direct-handle iMessage media sends through chat resolution plus `send-attachment`\n- split captioned iMessage media into attachment delivery followed by a normal text send\n- keep explicit chat media-only attachment routing covered, and add regressions for direct media plus captions\n\nCloses #87597\n\n## Tests\n- `node_modules/.bin/vitest run extensions/imessage/src/send.test.ts --environment node --reporter=dot`\n  - 26 passed\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Ran PR-head code locally at `652cb41a6e` against the authorized iMessage bot bridge, using a direct-handle target with all personal identifiers redacted from this PR.\n- Media-only direct send used `send-attachment` and produced an outgoing `image/png` row with `missing:false` in bot-visible Messages history.\n- Captioned direct media send used `send-attachment` for the image, then sent the caption as a separate normal text row. Bot-visible history showed the expected sequence: outgoing `image/png` with `missing:false`, followed by outgoing caption text.\n- The live proof intentionally avoids including phone numbers, real chat GUIDs, local user paths, or private message IDs.",
